# UI sigil config

A custom UI sigil should replace the default live tmux session marker.

    :bins jj cat

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', and 'cat' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :w .config/sesh/sesh.toml (written)
```toml
[ui]
sigil = "*"
```

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :t new-session -d -s alpha "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 80 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

The live session row should use the configured sigil.

    :snap

```terminal
session:
  3/3 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag
▌* alpha                                                                       ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

